author: Ben Kew
title: Russian MP Who Compared Putin’s Russia to Nazi Germany Publicly Assassinated in Ukraine
text: Graphic content / Ukrainian police experts examine the body of former Russian MP Denis Voronenkov after he was shot dead on March 23, 2017 in the center of Kiev. Ukrainian President blamed Russia for the murder of Voronenkov, who moved to Ukraine last year and was wanted by Russia for fraud, saying it was an 'act of state terrorism.' / AFP PHOTO / Sergei SUPINSKY (Photo credit should read SERGEI SUPINSKY/AFP/Getty Images)
